.TH LPF-RULES 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.3" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-rules \- show or diff generated backend rules
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf rules show <policy>
lpf rules diff \-\-observed <ruleset> <policy>
lpf rules diff \-\-live <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Render deterministic read\-only nftables rules from a checked lpf policy.
Diff rendered rules against observed lpf\-owned nftables table blocks.
Observed rules can be supplied from a file/stdin or read live with `nft list ruleset`.
This command does not apply host changes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-backend nftables
select nftables rendering; currently the only backend
.TP
\-\-observed <ruleset>
read observed nftables ruleset text from a file or \- for stdin
.TP
\-\-live
read observed nftables ruleset text with `nft list ruleset`
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf rules show fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
lpf rules diff \-\-observed current.nft fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
lpf rules diff \-\-live /etc/lpf.conf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-diff(8), lpf\-plan(8)
